---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Chefs | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Chefs working internationally, covering culinary careers abroad, restaurant industry, and global hospitality opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Chefs";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Chefs working abroad, creating cuisine internationally, and pursuing careers across restaurants, hotels, and culinary establishments worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/chef-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/chef-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Chef Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Chefs create culinary experiences through food preparation, menu development, and kitchen leadership. International chef careers span restaurant kitchens, hotel culinary operations, cruise ships, private yachts, and personal chef work for high-net-worth clients across the globe.
      </p>
      <p>
        International culinary opportunities exist through global hotel chains, international restaurant groups, cruise lines, resort properties, and private service networks that place chefs in kitchens worldwide.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Chefs working abroad across restaurants, hotels, and culinary establishments worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Chefs</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Variable by employer' },
          { need: 'Injury coverage', why: 'Burns, cuts, physical hazards', typical: 'Critical for profession' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Kitchen stress and pressure', typical: 'Important to include' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Physical demands', typical: 'Consider for long-term' },
          { need: 'Substance abuse support', why: 'Industry prevalence', typical: 'Consider carefully' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Physical career dependency', typical: 'Important protection' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Physical Hazards</h3>
      <p>
        Kitchen work involves significant physical hazards. Burns from heat and oil, cuts from knives, and slips in fast-paced environments are common. Coverage for occupational injuries is essential for chefs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Standing for extended periods, heavy lifting, and repetitive movements create musculoskeletal strain. Long-term physical demands require consideration for ergonomic and disability coverage.
      </p>

      <h3>Industry Culture</h3>
      <p>
        Kitchen culture has historically involved high stress, long hours, and unfortunately elevated rates of substance use and mental health challenges. Mental health support and substance abuse coverage are relevant considerations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Fine Dining</h3>
      <p>
        High-end restaurants. Benefits vary by restaurant. Intense environment. Fine dining offers prestige.
      </p>

      <h3>Hotels</h3>
      <p>
        Hotel culinary operations. Hotel chain benefits. Multiple outlets. Hotels offer structure.
      </p>

      <h3>Cruise Ships</h3>
      <p>
        Maritime culinary. Ship company coverage. Contract-based. Cruises offer travel.
      </p>

      <h3>Private Service</h3>
      <p>
        Private chef work. Coverage usually self-arranged. High compensation. Private offers flexibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Catering</h3>
      <p>
        Event catering operations. Catering company benefits. Variable schedules. Catering offers variety.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Chefs"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Chefs working abroad across restaurants, hotels, and culinary establishments worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Chef Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Culinary Education</h3>
      <p>
        Culinary school training. Degree programs. Professional certification. Education establishes foundation.
      </p>

      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Kitchen track record. Restaurant credits. Chef de partie to sous to executive progression. Experience is primary credential.
      </p>

      <h3>Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        ACF certifications. ServSafe credentials. Regional certifications. Certifications add credibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialization</h3>
      <p>
        Cuisine specialization. Pastry expertise. Dietary focus. Specialization defines niche.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Physical Injury</h3>
      <p>
        Burns and cuts common. Heat exposure. Sharp tools. Injury coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Standing and Lifting</h3>
      <p>
        Extended standing. Heavy pot lifting. Physical strain. Ergonomic coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Mental Health</h3>
      <p>
        High-pressure environment. Service intensity. Industry culture. Mental health support important.
      </p>

      <h3>Irregular Hours</h3>
      <p>
        Night and weekend shifts. Split schedules. Work-life challenges. Schedule impacts health.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Preparation</h3>
      <p>
        Mise en place. Ingredient preparation. Menu planning. Preparation enables service.
      </p>

      <h3>Service</h3>
      <p>
        Line cooking. Plate execution. Team coordination. Service delivers experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Management</h3>
      <p>
        Kitchen leadership. Staff management. Inventory control. Management sustains operations.
      </p>

      <h3>Development</h3>
      <p>
        Menu creation. Recipe development. Food costing. Development drives innovation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>International Opportunities</h3>
      <p>
        Global hotel positions. International restaurant groups. Cruise ships. Coverage must accommodate mobility.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Line cook to executive chef. Hotel culinary director. Restaurant ownership. Consulting. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Sustainability</h3>
      <p>
        Career physically demanding. Long-term health concerns. Transition planning. Sustainability considerations important.
      </p>

      <h3>Industry Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Sustainability focus growing. Dietary trends shifting. Technology integration. Adaptation needed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a chef considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Coverage varies significantly. Hotels better than independent restaurants. Physical hazard coverage important. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do restaurants provide good coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Varies widely. Large groups better. Independent restaurants often limited. Verify before accepting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is kitchen injury coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical for profession. Burns and cuts common. Occupational hazards real. Prioritize injury coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about cruise ship positions?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Ships typically provide coverage. Maritime regulations apply. Contract terms vary. Review ship coverage carefully.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Should I consider disability coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for physical careers. Kitchen work demands physical capability. Injury can end career. Protection important.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Hospitality growing globally. Fine dining evolving. New formats emerging. Positive with flexibility.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by understanding your specific employer's coverage provisions. Hotel and large restaurant group positions typically offer better benefits. Verify injury and mental health coverage. Consider long-term physical sustainability and disability protection.
      </p>
      <p>
        Chefs create culinary experiences that bring people together worldwide. Your coverage should support demanding, physical careers—addressing kitchen hazards, accommodating industry demands, and protecting your health across culinary positions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Culinary Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Chefs working abroad across restaurants, hotels, and culinary establishments worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
